    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Passenger Door Removal</title>
        <para>Removal of doors without removing drive arms:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the individual doors, disconnect the door opener drive rod brackets at the door to
                be removed.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate and remove the two mounting bolts on the drive rod door bracket located at the top of
                the door assembly, remove the door mounting bracket.
            </para>
            <figure id="f47006236" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg47/G47006236.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 236. Drive Rod Door Bracket</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. PASSENGER ENTRY DOOR OPENER- DOOR BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. PASSENGER ENTRY SECONDARY DOOR DRIVE ARM</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. PASSENGER ENTRY DOOR- FORWARD DOOR FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. DOOR DRIVE BRACKET MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With an assistant holding the door, lift the door up and out of the pivot block assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006237" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G47006237.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 237. Passenger Door Pivot Block Remove</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. DOOR PIVOT ROD INSERT HOLE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. PIVOT BLOCK COVER MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. PASSENGER ENTRY STEP</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Follow the same procedure to remove opposite passenger entry door.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
